The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Grasim inks cement deal in Orissa

 SUBRAT DAS 

 Bhubaneswar, Nov. 10: The Aditya Birla groups Grasim Industries signed MoUs with the Orissa government today to set up a 3.5-million-tonne integrated cement plant, which is expected to be the largest cement project in Orissa. 

 The plant will involve an investment of Rs 1,200 crore and will include a 50-mw captive thermal power plant with a split grinding unit, said S.K. Maheswari, group executive president of Aditya Birla group and chief manufacturing amp; project officer of the groups cement business. 

 Maheswari, who signed the MoU on behalf of Grasim Industries, said the project is expected to be commissioned in three years. Orissa Cement Ltd, based at Rajgangpur in Sundargarh district, will establish a 0.9-million-tonne per annum cement plant, a 60-mw captive power plant and a new kiln line of 4000 tonnes per day to produce clinker at existing cement plant with a total investment of Rs 850 crore. 

 Bengal-based ASO Cement has also signed a deal to set up a 0.5-million-tonne cement plant. 




